Abengoa to Develop 64 Megawatts of Wind Parks in Brazil

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-09-30T06:45:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/abengoa-to-develop-64-megawatts-of-wind-parks-in-brazil.html
Abengoa SA (ABG) , the Spanish engineering
farm that builds solar-thermal power generators and bioethanol
plants, won a contract to develop 64 megawatts of wind farms in
 Brazil .  Abengoa, based in Seville,  Spain , will build three wind
parks for the Brazilian National Electricity Agency in Ceara
State and maintain them for 20 years, the company said in an e-
mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Sills at 
 bsills@bloomberg.net  